---
description: Electron main, preload, IPC, bridge and process security rules
globs:
  - "app/main/**"
  - "app/preload/**"
  - "packages/contracts/**"
  - "packages/local-bridge/**"
  - "packages/process-supervisor/**"
alwaysApply: false
---

- Use domain-specific typed IPC with runtime validation; never expose generic invoke or Electron primitives.
- Never reveal credentials, PID, backend port, executable path, filesystem, or raw process access to the renderer.
- Renderer code never calls localhost; Electron main owns engine lifecycle and bridge access.
- Preserve sandboxing, context isolation, disabled Node integration, navigation and permission controls.
- Fail closed on invalid input, sender, identity, compatibility, or authentication.
- Redact secrets and return stable structured errors without sensitive detail.
- Clean up every subscription and lifecycle listener; test invalid input, teardown, and security boundaries.
